      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COOL NIGHT (3) produced another good effort at his latest appearance when he came from a couple of spots wider and raced parked but stuck on for third, beaten 3.5 metres. Came from the back row when winning here prior so is in good form and is likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. CHARGE AHEAD (5) was easy in betting first up but wasn't disgraced in finishing midfield after covering ground. That was his first outing for six months so it should have improved him and he was a Group 1 placegetter in Sydney last season so has the talent when right. HOT ROD HARRY (4) could be close to a win after finishing runner-up in two of his last three starts here, coming from this barrier to go under by 2m last week. CHECKNOUTTHETALENT (8) is in the mix following a respectable second at his most recent appearance at this circuit and distance, coming from this barrier to miss by 2.2m.",
